<s> A data model says what information is to be contained in a database, how the information will be used, and how the items in the database will be related to each other.  </s>
<s> For example, a data model might specify that a customer is represented by a customer name and credit card number and a product as a product code and price, and that there is a one-to-many relation between a customer and a product.  </s>
<s> It can be difficult to change a database layout once code has been written and data inserted.  </s>
