<s> A data modelling language is a mathematical formalism with a notation for describing data structures and a set of operations used to manipulate and validate that data.  </s>
<s> One of the most widely used methods for developing data models is the entity-relationship model.  </s>
<s> The relational model is the most widely used type of data model.  </s>
<s> Another example is NIAM.  </s>
